    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Recursion Demo</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            margin: 20px;\n        }\n        \n        #factorial-result {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n            font-size: 20px;\n            color: green;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Recursion Demonstration</h1>\n<p>Recursion is a technique in programming where a function calls itself in order to solve a problem.</p>\n\n<label for=\"number-input\">Enter a non-negative integer:</label>\n<input type=\"number\" id=\"number-input\" min=\"0\">\n<button id=\"calculate-button\">Calculate Factorial</button>\n\n<div id=\"factorial-result\"></div>\n\n<script>\n    function factorial(n) {\n        if (n === 0 || n === 1) {\n            return 1;\n        } else {\n            return n * factorial(n - 1);\n        }\n    }\n\n    document.getElementById('calculate-button').addEventListener('click', function() {\n        const numberInput = document.getElementById('number-input').value;\n        const number = parseInt(numberInput);\n\n        if (number < 0) {\n            document.getElementById('factorial-result').innerText = 'Please enter a non-negative integer.';\n        } else {\n            const result = factorial(number);\n            document.getElementById('factorial-result').innerText = `Factorial of ${number} is: ${result}`;\n        }\n    });\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
